Senate Resolution 474
By: Senators Orrock of the 36th, Dixon of the 45th, Harbison of the 15th, Burns of the 23rd
and Harrell of the 40th
ADOPTED SENATE
A RESOLUTION
1 Creating the Senate Study Committee on Higher Education Affordability; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Georgia has the third highest graduate and undergraduate student loan debt per
4 borrower in the nation; and
5 WHEREAS, by 2031, 72 percent of all jobs will require postsecondary credentials and
6 currently Georgia has a postsecondary completion rate of 50.8 percent among young adults;
7 and
8 WHEREAS, unlike many other states, Georgia does not have a means tested scholarship
9 program; and
10 WHEREAS, the amount of unrestricted education lottery reserves currently totals $1.6
11 billion; and
12 WHEREAS, this body should explore options for making higher education more affordable
13 for Georgians, including the creation of a means tested scholarship program.
